The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to neuroimaging data, specifically for predicting age from structural brain images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the need for novel CNN architectures tailored to brain images, which could fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed architecture using mean absolute error (MAE), which could fall under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
